Your package pypoppler failed to build from source in current rawhide.
http://koji.fedoraproject.org/koji/taskinfo?taskID=12857875
For details on mass rebuild see https://fedoraproject.org/wiki/Fedora_24_Mass_Rebuild

This bug appears to have been reported against 'rawhide' during the Fedora 24 development cycle. Changing version to '24'.
More information and reason for this action is here: https://fedoraproject.org/wiki/Fedora_Program_Management/HouseKeeping/Fedora24#Rawhide_Rebase
This build failure is caused by an upstream change in poppler, see https://bugs.freedesktop.org/show_bug.cgi?id=93229

Created attachment 1151782 Remove PopplerOrientation binding from pypoppler
This patch fixes pdfshuffler startup for me. According to poppler upstream, the PopplerOrientation API was unused, so removing it from the python binding might be acceptable. I haven't tried to check if pypoppler users are trying to use this API. If we want to keep this API in the python binding, https://cgit.freedesktop.org/poppler/poppler/commit/?id=38796894f8ab will have to be reverted from the poppler package.

(In reply to Christophe Fergeau from comment #6) > This patch fixes pdfshuffler startup for me.
And it fixes the build failure reported in this bug as well.

Created attachment 1174922 Patch for 0.12.2 which is currently in rawhide
Updated patch so that it works with pypoppler 0.12.2. Tested pdfshuffler startup with it.
